onist to the brink of a disaster in a provincial Russian town. Attempting to collect overdue royalties from a Moscow publisher, the expatriate writer tips his hat to Kafka. The book’s six interconnected tales are held together by the memorist’s imperative to make the ordinary absurd and the absurd-ordinary. Shrayer parses a translingual literary life filled with travel, politics, and discovery-and sustained by family love and faith in art’s transcendence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthors, Americany20th centuryvBiography. 0aImmigrantszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aAmerican:literature.  aJewish.  aKafka.  aRussian.  aSoviet-era.  aimmigrant.  amemoirs.  atravels.  aémigré.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102354008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2z978311117804208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z9783111318264oZDB-23-DSP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978164469999740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644699997423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781644699997/original  a978-3-11-102354-0  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-117804-2  DG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2b2023  a978-3-11-131918-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_